  "prompt": "What is the best way to tease your hair?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for teasing (or \"backcombing\") hair:\n\n1. Use the right tools\n- Fine-toothed comb\n- Soft bristle brush\n- Hair spray\n\n2. Preparation\n- Start with dry hair\n- Use slightly dirty hair (not freshly washed)\n- Apply heat protectant if using styling tools\n\n3. Technique\n- Section hair into smaller parts\n- Hold hair section straight up\n- Start at the roots\n- Use comb to push hair downward toward the scalp\n- Repeat backcombing motion 3-4 times per section\n- Gently smooth top layer for a more polished look\n- Use hairspray to set the volume\n\n4. Tips for different hair types\n- Fine hair: Use less aggressive teasing\n- Thick hair: Can handle more intense backcombing\n- Add texturizing spray for extra hold\n\n5. Maintenance\n- Don't tease hair too often to prevent damage\n- Use a gentle brush when removing teased style\n- Deep condition regularly\n\nRemember to be gentle and use proper technique to avoid damaging your hair.",
